==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Medusoid
<hw>Me*du"soid</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Medusa</ets>
+ <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Like a medusa; having
the fundamental structure of a medusa, but without a locomotive disk; --
said of the sessile gonophores of hydroids.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos>
<def>A sessile gonophore. See <xex>Illust.</xex> under
<er>Gonosome</er>.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Meech</ent>⟦br⟧
